  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Nouns of Time and Place",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الزمان واسم المكان",
      "content": [
        "Nouns of time (اسم الزمان) and place (اسم المكان) are derived from verbs to indicate when or where an action occurs.",
        "For Form I verbs, the patterns are مَفْعَل and مَفْعِل. The choice depends on the vowel of the middle letter in the present tense."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern مَفْعَل: for verbs with فَعَلَ يَفْعُلُ or فَعَلَ يَفْعَلُ",
        "Pattern مَفْعِل: for verbs with فَعَلَ يَفْعِلُ",
        "Same form for both time and place (context determines meaning)",
        "Derived forms use pattern مُفَعَّل، مُفَاعَل، etc."
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مَكْتَبٌ", "english": "office / desk (place of writing)" },
        { "arabic": "مَوْعِدٌ", "english": "appointment (time of promise)" },
        { "arabic": "مَلْعَبٌ", "english": "playground (place of playing)" },
        { "arabic": "مَدْخَلٌ", "english": "entrance (place of entering)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Derived Form Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "أوزان الأفعال المزيدة",
      "content": [
        "For derived verb forms (II-X), the noun of time/place follows the pattern of the passive participle (اسم المفعول).",
        "This makes it identical in form to the passive participle, with context distinguishing the meaning."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Form II: مُفَعَّل (e.g., مُعَلَّم - place of teaching)",
        "Form III: مُفَاعَل (e.g., مُسَافَر - travel destination)",
        "Form IV: مُفْعَل (e.g., مُرْسَل - sending place)",
        "Form V-X: follow passive participle pattern"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مُنْطَلَقٌ", "english": "starting point (Form VII)" },
        { "arabic": "مُلْتَقَى", "english": "meeting place (Form VIII)" },
        { "arabic": "مُسْتَشْفَى", "english": "hospital (Form X - place of seeking cure)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
